The '''Ephorate of Underwater Antiquities''' (the Greek Agency for Marine Archaeology) is a department within the [[Greek Ministry of Culture]]. [[Katerina Delaporta]] is the director of this agency. Permission from the EUA is needed to conduct surveys and photography dives on architectural structures, such as shipwrecks, in Greek waters.


