{{Infobox road |country=NPL |marker_image=[[File:H08-NP.png|x70px]] |name= Koshi Highway |translation= कोशी राजमार्ग |image =Koshi Highway at Bhedetar.jpg |alt = Koshi Highway at Bhedetar |caption = Koshi Highway at Bhedetar |length_km= |terminus_a = Rani, [[Biratnagar]] |terminus_b = [[Kimathanka]], [[Sankhuwasabha District|Sankhuwasabha]] |junction = |destinations= [[Biratnagar]], [[Itahari]], [[Dharan, Nepal|Dharan]], [[Bhedetar]], [[Hile]], [[Num, Nepal|Num]] |ahn= }}
'''Koshi Highway''' ({{lang-ne|कोशी राजमार्ग}}) or '''NH-08''' is a 390&nbsp;km long planned highway located in [[Province No. 1]] of [[Nepal]]. It is north-south highway which is understood to be shortest highway which connects [[India]] to [[China]] across the Himalayan mountains in Nepal.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://kathmandupost.ekantipur.com/news/2016-12-07/khandbari-kimathanka-road-na-airlifts-heavy-duty-vehicles-to-project-site.html |title= Khandbari-Kimathanka road: NA airlifts heavy duty vehicles to project site |date=7 Dec 2016 |website=www.kathmandupost.ekantipur.com |publisher=[[Kantipur Media Group]] |access-date=4 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://thehimalayantimes.com/nepal/biratnagar-kimathanka-trilateral-road-projects-disheartening-progress/ |title= Biratnagar-Kimathanka trilateral road project’s disheartening progress |date=10 Jan 2018 |website=www.thehimalayantimes.com |publisher= |access-date=4 May 2018}}</ref> Rani at [[Biratnagar]] is starting point of the road<ref name ="kimbir">{{cite web |url= https://article.wn.com/view/2018/01/10/BiratnagarKimathanka_trilateral_road_project_s_disheartening/ |title= Biratnagar-Kimathanka trilateral road project’s disheartening progress |date= |website=www.article.wn.com |publisher= |access-date=4 May 2018}}</ref> which is connected to [[Jogbani]] in [[India]] and [[Kimathanka]] is the end point of the Koshi highway, which is situated close to Chinese border.<ref name="kimbir"/>
