'''''Poliţia Locală''''' ({{IPA-ro|poliˈt͡si.a loˈkalə}}) is the generic name for the local [[police]] in [[Romania]] - on city or [[Communes of Romania|commune]] level. They are subordinated to the mayors and their main duties are to enforce the local ordinances and to assist the [[Romanian Police|National Police]] and the [[Gendarmerie (Romania)|Gendarmerie]] in maintaining and restoring the public order.
Is the local administration Police Departament and it has responsibilities relating to public order and tranquility, road traffic, street video surveillance, control of commercial companies from all fields, control on protection of the environment and salubrity as well as in the field of discipline construction. It also has a Department which authorises commercial activities of all types in its area.

